Uyo Senatorial District Leaders Forum (USDLF)  has called for transparent conduct of the coming party primaries in  Akwa Ibom State to avoid heating up the polity. This resolution was reached at the meeting of the group held weekend in Uyo, Akwa Ibom State chaired by Obong Engr. Ofiong Usen Akpabio and Obong Kingsley Peters Secretary-General. Comprising stakeholders and leaders of thought from nine local governments under Akwa Ibom North-East Senatorial District, the forum stressed the need for elections to be conducted maturely without rancor in accordance with the tenets of democracy to avoid heating up the polity 2023: Admit Shortcomings, Shun Propaganda In Campaign –… 2023: Afegbua Blasts Anti-Zoning Proponents, Says It’s… The forum further demanded broadening of the political space to accommodate all shades of views and interests. They believe it will promote participation, bring about a greater sense of belonging as well as ensure peace and tranquility in the Senatorial District, Akwa Ibom State and Nigeria as a whole. The Forum also prayed for the unity, peace and continued growth of the Akwa Ibom North-East (Uyo) Senatorial District, Akwa Ibom State and Nigeria as a whole throughout the political campaigns and the 2023 General elections and beyond USDLF used the occasion to commend Mr. Udom Gabriel Emmanuel, Governor of Akwa Ibom State for the prevalence of peace in the State and for the numerous developmental projects of his administration and called for collaborative support with Government in order to accelerate the success of its Completion Agenda.